A comet can fall into the Sun. The SOHO spacecraft has observed many suicidal comets. A comet, called a sungrazer, may pass so close to the Sun that the tidal forces will fragment the comet into several pieces. Or a comet may simply evaporate after a close encounter. Comets have also been known to be ejected from the solar system as they are sling-shotted around the Sun.
